import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='country', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude across the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Country', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=country_counts.index, y=country_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the most common country in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
